which might not be the active class. I wonder if \\\"Focus active class only\\\" would help direct to `Messages.message`. The public API using DateConverter also implies that only active classes are involved, and it seems to cover both calls and ResourceBundle in Messages. I’ll keep an eye on checkstyle for any potential line wrapping issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering import order**\\n\\nI’m thinking that maybe Checkstyle prefers static imports to appear before non-static ones? In the existing file, that doesn't seem to be the case, which is fine. I want to make my note final and concise though. I’ll need to mention the added file but remember that I didn’t run tests due to instructions. This way, I’ll keep everything clear for anyone who looks into this later on.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Added dedicated coverage test for `joptsimple.internal.Messages`:\n\n- `tests/src/net.sf.jopt-simple/jopt-simple/5.0.4/src/test/java/net_sf_jopt_simple/jopt_simple/JoptsimpleInternalMessagesTest.java`\n\nThe test exercises `DateConverter` failure formatting, which reaches `Messages.message(...)` and its remaining uncovered `ResourceBundle#getBundle(String, Locale)` call site while staying outside the library package and avoiding reflection.\n\nPer instruction, I did not compile or run tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08a3f2a7446e8af80169f4f790975c8195b9ccdf304a2a6da3\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1056, "output": 665, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40121, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777661825800, "responseId": "resp_08a3f2a7446e8af80169f4f7823ed481958b63095a5a573795"}, "toolResults": []}
